  31,12,"Indeed, We blessed Luqm√Ęn with wisdom, ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúBe grateful to Allah, for whoever is grateful, it is only for their own good. And whoever is ungrateful, then surely Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy.‚ÄĚ"
  31,13,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Luqm√Ęn said to his son, while advising him, ‚ÄúO my dear son! Never associate ňĻanythingňļ with Allah ňĻin worshipňļ, for associating ňĻothers with Himňļ is truly the worst of all wrongs.‚ÄĚ"
